<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-07-27T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-07-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="720" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d720">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">894c.20/2: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-07-27T16:00:00-04:00">July 27, 1934—4
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>126. Reference Dairen’s despatch to you dated June 29, 1934,<note n="9" xml:id="d720fn9">Not printed.</note> subject “Foreign Firms
                            Requested to Contribute towards Air Defense of Dairen.”</p>
                        <p>Please ascertain from Vincent<note n="10" xml:id="d720fn10">John Carter
                                Vincent, Consul at Dairen.</note> the present status of this matter
                            and report by telegraph as soon as possible.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>